rst tested way back in the &#8216;50s and &#8216;60s (many such cases in ha=
rd tech).&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>If the phrases &#8220;nuclear re=
actor&#8221; and &#8220;experimentation&#8221; sound odd together, well, it=
 was a different time. Back then, nuclear reactors were governed by the Ato=
mic Energy Commission (AEC), which was tasked with both regulating and prom=
