t-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.62=
5em 0; position: relative;"><strong>Coolant</strong></h3><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
<span>Per the requirement, Kaleidos is not a light water reactor, but a </s=
pan><strong>high-temperature gas-cooled reactor</strong><span>. In this cas=
e, the gas is </span><strong>helium</strong><span>. Helium serves as the </=
span><strong>coolant</strong><span>. Here&#8217;s how it works:&#160;</span=
></p><div class=3D"captioned-image-container-static" style=3D"font-size: 16=
